Context

Earlier hardening work should already have:
- improved API/public-surface truth
- clarified strict verification vs salvage boundaries
- centralized refusal mapping in reporting
- made reporting/output flows depend on a canonical verification model
- removed output-layer dependence on raw internal format structs

What remains is the unfinished internal typing debt:

- pack/salvage metadata builders still use dynamic metadata construction in some active paths
- classification/metadata derivation still risks drift unless all remaining active paths converge on typed structures
- verify/report truth remains vulnerable if these upstream paths are not completed

This packet finishes that work.

---------------------------------------------------------------------

Hard constraints

- Do NOT weaken strict extraction semantics.
- Do NOT add new format features.
- Do NOT reintroduce raw internal-struct leakage into output/reporting paths.
- Do NOT leave `serde_json::Value` in active pack/salvage metadata construction paths once this packet is complete.
- Do NOT broaden public surfaces such as `crushr::format` or `crushr::index_codec` beyond what current in-repo consumers already require.
- Do NOT bypass the canonical verification model established by earlier packets.
- Refusal mapping remains centralized and exhaustive; if new refusal variants are introduced in this packet, slug mapping must be updated in the same patch.

